ProtoResult:
. "If $z^n = 1$, then the $n$th roots of unity are \[ z = 
   \operatorname{cis}\left( \frac{2 k \pi}{n } \right), \] 
   where $k = 0, 1, \ldots, n-1$. Furthermore, the $n$th roots 
   of unity form a cyclic subgroup of ${\mathbb T}$ of order 
   $n$."
